Text.Value: I want to know why you're harbouring Ironhand Gnomes in your cellar.
The Gondians think they're the only ones fit to swing a hammer round here. They're wrong. One day they'll learn that the hard way.
A liar AND a thug. It's time someone beat some bloody respect into you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Tense, ready to fight the player

Text.Value: Hard enough trying to make a bloody living without some moron cracking your skull for no good reason.
My shopkeeper can tell you more. Give the lazy sod something to do for once.

EditorData.NodeContext: dismissing you - this is a waste of time

Text.Value: You! Try attacking me when my back isn't turned, you bloody coward!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The smith comes running out of the smithy, one hand to the back of his head, the other clutching an iron bar like a weapon. He spots the player - accuses them.

Text.Value: You were attacked by a doppelganger. She was impersonating me.
Don't dare lie to me. I saw you with my own eyes, grinning at me like some bloody imbecile.
I'm telling you, it was a doppelganger!
Those gnomes are victims. They've spent years in exile, no forge to call their own, all because of some ancient bloody grudge.
Well, given this is in fact a blacksmiths, we sell things that need smithing.
You must have been attacked by my twin. She's a real handful.
You must have been attacked by my twin. He's a real handful.
You must have been attacked by my twin. They're a real handful.
Oh Gods be damned, I don't know. I'd have sworn but - my head's pounding, I don't remember.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still annoyed, but accepting he can't prove anything.

Text.Value: Is that so? You've got some evil twin running round whacking people round the back of the head?

EditorData.NodeContext: Furious, and NOW you're lying to him

Text.Value: You had a blow to the head. Are you sure you're remembering correctly?
Now clear off. You want anything else - go to the shop. I've got work to do.
Leave.
What do you sell?
Watch your tone. No one speaks to me that way.
I- I don't need to. I know what you did, whacking me over the head. Near caved my skull in!
I want to trade.
What do you want now?

EditorData.NodeContext: Not happy  - "why the hell are you still bothering me?"

Text.Value: Brave words for a man harbouring wanted terrorists in his cellar.
You're not wrong. Feels like my brain's been drawn on the anvil.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He slumps, putting a hand to his head.

Text.Value: Please - keep bothering me. I've no work to get on with.
I need a bloody drink. Go on - clear off. I've seen enough of your face today.

EditorData.NodeContext: Final - I'm done with the conversation

Text.Value: Until that happens, I'll give those Ironhands a roof over their heads. Nothing wrong with it.
Leave.
I tell you now - you'll be seeing bloody double when I'm done with you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Physically threatening in some way (e.g. pointing a finger at the player)

Text.Value: Go on - take your thuggery elsewhere. Bloody animal.
I'm going to knock that smirk right off your face.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Physically threatening in some way (e.g. pointing a finger at the player)

Text.Value: And we both know who bloody gave them to me, don't we?
Now you're acting innocent are you? After you near caved my bloody skull in?
If you're a customer, go down to the shop. Otherwise - clear off.
Well - I - I'm sure it was you. Almost certain...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Relaxes a little - he's accepted you're not the one responsible.
EditorData.NodeContext: Thrown - aggressive but losing confidence fast

Text.Value: What in the nine Hells are you talking about?
Then go down to the bloody shop. I've got work to do.
Go on. Say that again. Like you really, really mean it...
Spoken like the vicious scum you are.
Been poking around downstairs have you? Well I've got nothing to hide.
You know what? Not worth it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The blacksmith drops his guard, adopts a more peaceful stance
EditorData.NodeContext: Scared, but trying to sound like he's still in control

Text.Value: I know it's hard to believe, but you really were attacked by a doppelganger.
Hallucinations. Irrational anger. These are symptoms of a serious head injury.
Oh, I'm very sorry. If you're offended, feel free to make a complaint.
Well, you'd better knock some sense into that bloody thug, before I do.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Relaxes a little - he's accepted you're not the one responsible.
EditorData.NodeContext: Still threatening, but knows you're not responsible

Text.Value: Try it, and you'll be smiling without teeth for the rest of your life.
I didn't attack you - I've been out here the whole time.
I want to know why you're harbouring Ironhand Gnomes in your cellar.
Terrorists? Is that why you belted me over the head?

Synopsis: Gyldro Angleiron the Smith unknowingstly was knocked unconcious by Orin the Red.  He only awakes once Orin the Red has teleported away - leaving the players with the awkward circumstance of being at his smithy.  He views the players with suspicion until convinced either-wise.
